   <abstract>In the 1920s, the Knoxville Sentinel maintained a board that allowed fans to keep up with the World Series game. It was manned by two boys%3A one (seen near the policeman's perch) relayed news to the crowd via megaphone, and the other (seen at the bottom of the board) updated the posted score. In this 1921 event, the Giants beat the Yankees 5-3.</abstract>
